Wrap the text in a given width

>PROBLEM

You are given a string string and an integer max_width.

Your task is to wrap the string into a paragraph of width max_width.

Sample Input:
ABCDEFGHIJKLIMNOQRSTUVWXYZ
4
Sample Output:
ABCD
EFGH
IJKL
IMNO
QRST
UVWX
YZ

>SOLUTION

import textwrap

def wrap(string, max_width):
    
        
    wp = textwrap.wrap(string,width=max_width)
        
    return "\n".join(wp)
        
    

if __name__ == '__main__':
    string, max_width = input(), int(input())
    result = wrap(string, max_width)
    print(result)
